{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JTQ1RQZpBhnRm7HdCVr21W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n- The demo-app deployment uses `app: demo-app` label selector\n- It runs busybox httpd on port 5678, serving `/www/index.html` which contains \"hello\"\n- The app only serves the root path \"/\"\n\nI need to:\n1. Create a Service that targets port 5678 on pods with label `app: demo-app`\n2. Create an Ingress with nginx ingress class that exposes `http://secure.example.com/api` and rewrites the path to `/` since the app only serves \"/\"\n\nThe test curl is:\n```bash\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- curl -sS -H \"Host: secure.example.com\" http://ingress-nginx-controller.ingress-nginx.svc/api\n```\n\nSince the app only serves `/` but we need to expose it at `/api`, I need to use path rewriting with the nginx ingress annotation `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /` and set the ingress path to `/api`.\n\nNow I'll set up the ingress resources with the proper path configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1048,"cache_read_input_tokens":28444,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1048},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56c9fc8e-871e-4bdf-afd0-54d6fb532082","uuid":"2dd320e9-135f-4a56-9af6-3aa784e56bd1","request_id":"req_011CcahsXjaYkzs5SeYWMqwo"}
